  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C" class="c1">Ok fellow Clerics, here's the lowdown on the spawning of Zordak Ragefire.  He used to be a 24 hour spawn after Naggy was dead, probably would spawn after the last Fire Giant was killed.  He is now a 0 to 72 hour spawn after Naggy dies.  We killed Naggy, then came back 24 hours later, cleared the Fire Giants, and low and behold, no Zordak !  I camped a friend's Bard in the 'safe corner' near the stairs up to the lair, approximately 32 hours after we killed Naggy, Zordok was up !  He is no longer a 24 hour spawn, but now a 0 to 72 hour spawn.  Some hints as to killing him :   The merchant, who is the ph, and who you give your pearl to, is non aggro.  When you give the pearl to him, he will attack you !  Have Warriors nearby to taunt him off you or he will kick yer butt !  When the changed merchant dies, the DRAGON spawns IMMEDIATELY !  The problem here is, you will have used some mana in killing the merchant.  A friend suggested (and I agree)  that when the dragon spawns, run away from him.. if he is not hurt at all, he will probaly not summon anyone.   He will get stuck in the door, and you can med to full.  Then, send in tanks first, with Clerics in the back to heal them (NASTY fire based spells.. get up yer resists), and hopefully a few Bards along for some resists also.  When he is properly hurt (we usually do this when the mob is half dead or so)send in the casters.    I hope this works for everyone, and I wish people would be more free with thier information.  I asked several people who had done the quest and who had been helping with it, and noone would lend me a bit of advice.  As a result, my guild and several dozen friends wasted all day saturday clearing FG (we got decent exp there tho at least :)  But, sadly, after slaughtering us all, the DRAGON despawned (he was severely bugged, and kept summoning us even after we had died several times, I believe he has a HUGE aggro radius).  Again, there are enough greedy folks in the 'real world', lets help eachother out in Eq, it is a game after all, and we're all here to have fun !<br><br></td></tr>
